xenbase is a model organism database (mod), providing informatics resources, as well as genomic and biological data on xenopus frogs.xenbase has been available since 1999, and covers both x. laevis and x. tropicalis xenopus varieties. as of 2013 all of its services are running on virtual machines in a private cloud environment, making it one of the first mods to do so. other than hosting genomics data and tools, xenbase supports the xenopus research community though profiles for researchers and laboratories, job and events postings, and a number of discussion forums at .